word_mean_info__list.difference: 多指在音乐、书法、演讲等方面所进行的比赛或竞争。其结果，由评判委员会裁决。
通常指体育运动项目的比赛，隐含势均力敌意味。
多指体育运动中的各项比赛、角逐，也指知识、技巧等方面的竞赛。

bilingual.source: In some families, competition starts very young.
bilingual.target: 在一些家庭中，竞争从很小就开始。

bilingual.source: The competitor is cowing the new business to reduce competition.
bilingual.target: 竞争者在威胁新企业以减少竞争。

bilingual.source: He was elected in a tough competition.
bilingual.target: 他在激烈的竞争中当选。

bilingual.source: The competition in the market is fierce.
bilingual.target: 市场上的竞争是激烈的。
市场竞争促使价格下降。

bilingual.source: The competition in the market is ruthless.
bilingual.target: 市场上的竞争是无情的。
内部的公司竞争非常激烈。

bilingual.source: The competition is getting more and more fierce.
The intense competition made him feel sket.
bilingual.target: 激烈的竞争让他感到紧张。

list.abstract: 竞争，是一个汉语词语，意思是为了自己方面的利益而跟人争胜。

yingyinNormal.en: What are you doing? He's your competition.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你干什么啊？他要跟你竞争的。

yingyinNormal.en: I suspect not for long. Meet the competition.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但我不再是了，来看看竞争对手。

yingyinNormal.en: In competition, individual ambition serves the common good.
yingyinNormal.zh: “在竞争中，个人的雄心是为了公共的利益。”

yingyinNormal.en: At first, I was nervous about the competition, and then I became my own competition.
yingyinNormal.zh: 起初，我害怕与人竞争，后来我的竞争对手变成了自己。

yingyinNormal.en: We have to look at the competition and say we're gonna do it differently.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们会对竞争对手说，我们还可以做出不同的东西来

yingyinNormal.en: And we can't look at the competition and say we're gonna do it better.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们不能在面对竞争对手的时候才开始说我们会做得更好的

yingyinNormal.en: The risk of unpopular decision, competition, corruption, passivity, have prevented any action.
yingyinNormal.zh: 决定可能引发的不满，竞争，腐败以及不作为阻断了任何行动。

yingyinNormal.en: Fear of foreign competition once led countries to try and produce everything they needed and impose heavy taxes to keep out foreign goods.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对外国竞争感到的恐惧让一些国家决定自给自足，自行生产所有产品，并且向国外的商品收相当重的税。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, Alex and Sanjay, after four years of spirited competition, I am very pleased to tell you that you are the Pali High class of 2015 co-valedictorians!
yingyinNormal.zh: 艾丽克斯和桑杰，在四年的激烈竞争之后，我很高兴地告诉你们，你们俩将成为巴利高中2015届的联合学生代表！

yingyinNormal.en: It's a tough program, Ender. When they brought me to this country, there was less competition. And still, I didn't make it. You have nothing to be ashamed of. Nothing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那个项目非常困难，安德，他们带我来到这个国家时，竞争还没现在激烈，我都没能通过，你没什么好羞愧的，没必要。

yingyinNormal.en: And Emma needs a cowgirl outfit for the competition.
yingyinNormal.zh: 爱玛得穿牛仔装！

yingyinNormal.en: The Pet Competition
yingyinNormal.zh: 宠物竞赛

yingyinNormal.en: It's not a competition.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这可没什么可比的。

yingyinNormal.en: A singing competition? Who wants to see another one of those?
yingyinNormal.zh: 大型歌手大赛？现在谁还看这种东西？

yingyinNormal.en: The Scare what now? The Scare Games! A super-intense Scaring competition!
yingyinNormal.zh: 惊吓什么？惊吓杯！超激烈的惊吓比赛

yingyinNormal.en: There is also a final signup for next week's scholastic decathlon competition.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还有下个礼拜，学术全能竞赛，最后报名即将截止。

yingyinNormal.en: As a student, I created these games as a friendly competition, but be prepared.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我在学生时代创立这些比赛作为友谊竞赛。

yingyinNormal.en: Sophie's competition made a live-action North Pole workshop in front of her house.
yingyinNormal.zh: 苏菲的对手在她房子前做了一个实景圣诞礼物工厂。

yingyinNormal.en: So, what are some ways we could set our comic book store apart from the competition?
yingyinNormal.zh: 有什么办法能让我们的漫画书店在同行中脱颖而出？

yingyinNormal.en: He wanted to tell me he's gonna compete in some ultimate fighting competition thingy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他要参加一个什么终极格斗比赛。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

n. 竞争对手；竞争者；参赛者；比赛者
adj. 竞争的；竞争性的；可与…匹敌的；好竞争的；有竞争心的；有竞争力的

word_family.mean: v. 竞争；角逐；比赛；参赛；能匹敌；能对抗

sense_info_list.en: a situation in which people or organizations compete with each other for something that not everyone can have

examination_example.sentence: It protects against unfair <highlight>competition</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它防止不正当竞争。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Competition</highlight> law appears to be the only way to address these imbalances of power.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 竞争法似乎是解决这些权力失衡的唯一途径。

examination_example.sentence: For factory owners, it all adds up to stiff <highlight>competition</highlight> for workers – and upward pressure on wages.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对工厂主来说，这一切都意味着争夺工人的激烈竞争，以及工资上涨的压力。

sense_info_list.en: an event in which people compete with each other to find out who is the best at something

examination_example.sentence: Your prospects would be almost as dismal if arguments were even just <highlight>competitions</highlight> — like, say, tennis games.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果争论仅仅是比赛，比如网球比赛，你的前景几乎同样暗淡。

examination_example.sentence: focuses on mass <highlight>competition</highlight>
examination_example.sentence_trans: 关注大众比赛

sense_info_list.en: the person or people with whom one is competing, especially in a commercial or sporting

word_usage.usage:
competition, contest和match的区别：
(1) competition多指体育赛事、知识技巧方面的竞赛，也可指利益之争，如price competition价格竞争。
(2) contest多指在音乐、书法、演讲等方面所进行的比赛，结果多由评判委员会裁决，如a writing contest 写作比赛。
(3) match多指体育运动项目的比赛，隐含势均力敌意味，如a football match足球比赛。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 多指体育运动中的各项比赛、角逐, 也指知识、技巧等方面的竞赛。
多指在音乐、书法、演讲等方面所进行的比赛或竞争。其结果, 由评判委员会裁决。
指决定胜负的比赛, 多以个人对抗或集体对抗形式根据一定的规则进行。
通常指体育运动项目的比赛, 隐含势均力敌意味。

word_usage.usage:
competition, contest和match的区别：
(1) competition多指体育赛事、知识技巧方面的竞赛，也可指利益之争，如price competition价格竞争。
(2) contest多指在音乐、书法、演讲等方面所进行的比赛，结果多由评判委员会裁决，如a writing contest 写作比赛。
(3) match多指体育运动项目的比赛，隐含势均力敌意味，如a football match足球比赛。
